{
  "stem": "27509.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's a sort of, in the olden days-- even now, it takes most probably the length of the entire thing in those days.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- but he didn't last long because the war years, first World War years immediate-- immediately after the war, things went so bad that he-- he just couldn't carry on.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had to give it up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, he was.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Absolutely religious, in the most simple and most uncompromising way.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That it was the norm in those days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And although he did not have a father to instruct him in it, but the family tradition was in itself very compelling because it so happens that we belong to one of the most illustrious families in [INAUDIBLE] for the last 500 years.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Some of the most prominent Talmudic interpreters, people whose words and-- and work is included in the Talmud volumes, are our grandparents.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it went right down the line.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It went right down the line from the Mashhad.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I'm mentioning it on record on purpose because those who know would know what-- what it stands for.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the [INAUDIBLE], the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the entire line of the Brisk rabbis.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The Brisk Linear, it was called.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The Solovejcziks.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You know, Rabbi Solovejczik of-- of Boston, the-- the greatest authority of our generation, just passed away a few years ago.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That is the line of rabbis.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Rabbi Chaim Solovejczik was the chief rabbi of Warsaw, and so on to Solovejczik.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And when I was in 1940 in Lithuania, I was the guest of the chief rabbi of Lithuania, whose first name was the same as my uncle's name, my father's brother's name, Rov Avram Dov Shapiro.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the name of-- of Rabbi Shapiro, that-- known as the Kovno Rov, the Rabbi of Kovno, was renowned.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
